<br>
put in your ql125 treatment implants.  this will raise your treatment to enable you to put in ql150 surgery implants which will then allow you to put in ql175 and so on.<br>
<br>
when i put in implants, i put in my ql125 head, then ql168 eye, which then allows me to put in my ql175 head which i wasnt able to before.  this increases your treatment significantly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucson777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cson777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#660000>(1/3/02 1:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=435.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: remember that you can hop surgery implants</span><hr size=1> Yeah, but I don't know how many Shining Driving Head implants or Bright Lumping Eye implants I have over QL125. I've got a crap load of implants that are QL125+, but most are useless because they've got some useless cluster in them. I would love to find a QL 150 head implant with an empty shining slot.<br>
